5wzV4nvspsDiTqpadQU5av9Rovi7RhNhARr6hpNukEnCO3veFGBiZdPoSX1Wt_nYHYwjsOT_h0EbFEUfUT7p4-90fQDGC_aOEB5UfMByF3zFN-0bImWzifdAenOM68cC722hx2fDusgb1ChJ44PQKlOWMA7D7zoEwrXSjSP4O8BYcfVn4m6N_vezDHh8ZN8LzecaK8ClzZ0f-MXzdVFNkHsgj6uBA_2zarLDvFccQ3_XgOG49M_2RvDIPkNjNb9A1cjhfIqly6iCokCCtUJJ1UgSeLzKbqvK_S-QVXGFdmxPTvVwnkp_Vj5vRtykh33LiImxlQYWx4_g7cuNIxQuEUyzwAsGreK8UszuAEIP2otR3oBfV41k4PofSQlwzpx5jrlOgwNhw0M1njgVAdx0vno=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating web test support**\\n\\nIt looks like there's an issue with existing tests when using @WebAppConfiguration, mainly about loading the web context. The failure seems related to MergedContextConfigurationRuntimeHints for web resource base paths and the absence of servlets. If I'm looking to test with MockServletContext, I think I might need the servlet-api. I'm wondering if web test support is central to spring-test and how it all fits together!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"spring-test publishes only spring-core as a required dependency, but meaningful TestContext coverage normally uses Spring ApplicationContext APIs and the existing coverage exercises JUnit 4 integration; both are optional upstream integrations rather than transitive dependencies.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.springframework:spring-context:7.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The Spring TestContext Framework is normally used to load and manage Spring ApplicationContext/WebApplicationContext instances; upstream declares spring-context optional, and the existing tests already require ApplicationContext, GenericApplicationContext, and AOT context-loading APIs.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"junit:junit:4.13.2\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"spring-test includes JUnit 4 integration such as SpringJUnit4ClassRunner, which is optional upstream and is exercised by the existing coverage.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image, environment variable, or system property is required for baseline coverage. Prefer self-contained TestContext, annotation, mock environment, and AOT-hint tests. If testing AOT generation paths, account for Spring's native-image/AOT runtime guard instead of assuming processAheadOfTime is always allowed.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"spring-test contains many optional integrations; tests that intentionally cover MockMvc/mock web, Mockito bean overrides, reactive web support, HtmlUnit/Selenium, TestNG, or JDBC/transaction support may need additional targeted dependencies, but those are not required for baseline meaningful coverage.\",\n    \"The current failing assertion appears to be a Spring 7 behavior/API expectation issue rather than missing Docker or environment setup.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0500b890c253ba2c016a29236bd9ac819592578b2ad377fdf9\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1885, "output": 1047, "cacheRead": 37888, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 40820, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781080922701, "responseId": "resp_0500b890c253ba2c016a29235b5d108195b7eeb72f37deb1c0"}}
